│ THOUGHT: Perfect! Now I can see the issue. On line 9186-9187, the code adds all VFs in the `Range` to the plan:                                                                       │
│                                                                                                                                                                                       │
│ ```cpp                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ for (ElementCount VF : Range)                                                                                                                                                         │
│   Plan->addVF(VF);                                                                                                                                                                    │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│                                                                                                                                                                                       │
│ The problem is that the `Range` might have been modified (clamped) by the various `getDecisionAndClampRange` calls earlier in the function. If all these decisions exclude the scalar │
│ VF (VF=1), then the final range won't include it, and thus the plan won't have the scalar VF.                                                                                         │
│                                                                                                                                                                                       │
│ Looking at the test case, we have a loop with mixed integer widths (i64 induction variable truncated to i32). The vectorization cost model might be determining that the scalar VF is │
│ not viable for some reason, causing it to be excluded from the range.                                                                                                                 │
│                                                                                                                                                                                       │
│ The fix should ensure that even if the range gets clamped to exclude VF=1, we still add the scalar VF to at least one plan when there are multiple plans or VFs.                      │
│                                                                                                                                                                                       │
│ However, looking more carefully at the assertion in `computeBestVF`, it expects that when there are multiple plans or multiple VFs, at least one plan should have the scalar VF. The  │
│ proper fix is to ensure that the scalar VF is always included in the planning process.                                                                                                │
